# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if the
#   project is co-developed in multiple versions of Python.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if the platform is not the same, the lock file will be different.
#   Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, poetry.lock is generally recommended to be committed unless in certain environments.
#   poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv, pdm.lock is generally recommended to be committed unless in certain environments.
#   pdm.lock

